inalize the valid JSON, ensuring there’s no markdown within it.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No required setup beyond the existing Pekko actor artifact is needed for meaningful coverage. The resolved org.apache.pekko:pekko-actor_2.13:2.0.0-M1 POM only adds scala-library and com.typesafe:config transitively, and the classic ActorSystem/Props APIs are usable without Docker, external services, environment variables, or system properties.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment or system-property setup is required. The current failure is caused by tests using removed org.apache.pekko.actor.TypedActor/TypedProps/TypedActorExtension APIs: these classes are present in 1.1.5 but absent from the 2.0.0-M1 actor jar. Generate/update tests around still-present classic actor APIs such as ActorSystem, Props, Actor, scheduling, dispatchers, config, serialization helpers, or other APIs available in the resolved 2.0.0-M1 artifact. Pekko documentation lists pekko-testkit as a conventional test dependency, but it is optional for meaningful coverage because actor behavior can be exercised with plain actors plus futures/latches.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"If the generated tests intentionally use Pekko TestKit APIs, they will need org.apache.pekko:pekko-testkit_2.13:2.0.0-M1 as an additional test dependency, but this is not required by the library itself.\",\n    \"If tests target DNS resolver internals similar to the existing DnsSettingsTest, module export flags such as --add-exports=java.base/sun.net.dns=ALL-UNNAMED may be needed; ordinary actor-system coverage does not require this.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_025421d0155a9af6016a42f9dd22dc819395145329ab244e63\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2203, "output": 879, "cacheRead": 25600, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28682, "cost": {"inpu